data.title: Britney's psychic will look into her marriage
data.meta_description: NOW that newlyweds Jessica Simpson and Nick Lachey have finally split, celeb-watchers are focusing on another fascinating high-profile marriage: the union between Britney Spears and Kevin Federline.
data.text:
According to a report in the forthcoming issue of Life & Style magazine, Spears is so stressed out about the refusal of her spouse of 15 months to go into couples therapy that she's started seeking another man.

A psychic.

"She's willing to have a third party arbitrate the problems," a loose-lipped friend tells the magazine, revealing that when the singer asked Federline to join her in therapeutic sessions, he refused, saying: "That's for crazy people. If you want to see a shrink, go by yourself."

The source continues: "She wants to know if Kevin will cheat, if they'll have another child and if the marriage will last."

Spears, who is up for a role in the Broadway revival Sweet Charity, is also practising more retail therapy than usual these days.

Last week, on a jaunt to New York City, she hit the Michal Negrin jewellery store and dropped $30,000 in less than half an hour.

"She was sweet and polite," an employee reports. "She just came in and out."

For Brad is Jolie's good fellow BRAD Pitt and Angelina Jolie are denying intensifying rumours that she is with child, but at least the couple have stopped playing coy about their relationship.

Last week in Japan to promote the movie that started it all (Mr & Mrs Smith) the couple surprised reporters who attended a press conference by flirting heavily with each other.

Pitt started the ball rolling, telling the bemused hacks that Angelina is "very difficult to get along with on the set, a lot of star tantrums". Jolie came back at her beau by claiming, "He takes more time in hair and make-up than I do."

But Pitt, who appears to want the last word always, recovered quickly, adding: "It's true. I take more time. It's just preparing myself for the attitude. And I'd just

like to say, I would never do it again."

Mariska does her bit for baby boom THE Hollywood baby

boom shows no sign of slowing down. Just as reps for Ben Affleck and Jennifer Garner confirmed the safe arrival of the couple's new baby girl on Thursday night, there came word that Law & Order: SVU star Mariska Hargitay and her husband Peter Hermann are expecting their first child.

Hargitay, 41, who met

Hermann, 38, on the set

of the TV show, is the

daughter of silver-screen icon Jayne Mansfield,

who died in a car crash

in 1967.

Her dad, Hungarian bodybuilder and film actor Mickey Hargitay, sometimes pops up in cameo roles in L&O:SVU, which has the cast speculating about how long Mariska will wait before this tot takes to camera. Also expecting: Karen Elson, the model wife of guitar whiz Jack White.

Pammy invests in a new top PAMELA Anderson, the

former Baywatch babe who inadvertently became an internet video star and

then moved on to become

a cartoon heroine in

Stripperella,is back

on TV with a second

season of her aptly named sitcom Stacked. But Anderson, who plays party-girl-turned-bookstore-employee Skyler Dayton, is fed up with the trashy

sexpot threads she's

expected to wear and decided to forgo the

$25,000 worth of "skimpy wife beaters and ripped jeans" provided by the

producers and pay for her

own wardrobe.

"The people behind the show just wanted her to look like sex," says a snitch, "but Pam wanted more Sex and the City." To that end, Anderson - much to the chagrin

of several Hollywood wives - recently cleaned out

the Beverly Hills store

of her close friend,

Stella McCartney.

Striving for a more

elegant, classy look,

she spent $100,000

buying everything from sweaters to dresses and - naturally - Stella's trademark vegan pumps.
